{"number":58627,"title":"[MPG codegen] ToRequestContent not emitted for extensible-enum / union body parameters causes CS0117","body":"### Summary

The MPG code generator emits a call to `.ToRequestContent(payload)` for any **non-primitive** request body parameter, but only actually synthesizes the `ToRequestContent` helper method on **MRW model** types. When the body parameter type is an **extensible-enum / union struct** (or any non-MRW type), the helper is never generated, so the generated rest-operation method fails to compile with **CS0117: &#39;&#39; does not contain a definition for &#39;ToRequestContent&#39;**.

### Concrete repro — Azure.ResourceManager.Marketplace

- **Spec (TypeSpec)**: `specification/marketplace/resource-manager/Microsoft.Marketplace/Marketplace/routes.tsp`
  ```typespec
  interface PrivateStoreCollectionOperationGroup {
    @Azure.ResourceManager.Private.legacyResourceOperation(Collection, &#34;action&#34;)
    @route(&#34;/providers/Microsoft.Marketplace/privateStores/{privateStoreId}/collections/{collectionId}&#34;)
    @post
    post(
      ...ApiVersionParameter,
      @path privateStoreId: string,
      @path collectionId: string,
      @bodyRoot payload?: Operation,
    ): OkResponse | ErrorResponse;
  }
  ```
  `Operation` is an **extensible enum** defined in `models.tsp`:
  ```typespec
  union Operation {
    string,
    DeletePrivateStoreOffer: &#34;DeletePrivateStoreOffer&#34;,
    Ping: &#34;Ping&#34;,
    DeletePrivateStoreCollection: &#34;DeletePrivateStoreCollection&#34;,
    DeletePrivateStoreCollectionOffer: &#34;DeletePrivateStoreCollectionOffer&#34;,
  }
  ```

- **Legacy Swagger (for reference)**: `specification/marketplace/resource-manager/Microsoft.Marketplace/preview/2023-01-01-preview/privateStore.json` — same POST shape, `payload` has `$ref` to `Operation` enum with `x-ms-enum.modelAsString: true`.

- **Generated code (broken)**: `sdk/marketplace/Azure.ResourceManager.Marketplace/src/Generated/PrivateStoreCollectionInfoResource.cs`
  ```csharp
  public virtual Response Delete(PrivateStoreOperation? payload = default, CancellationToken cancellationToken = default)
  {
      // ...
      using var message = _restClient.CreateDeleteRequest(
          Id.SubscriptionId, Guid.Parse(Id.Name), Guid.Parse(Id.Parent.Name),
          PrivateStoreOperation.ToRequestContent(payload),   // &lt;-- CS0117 here
          context);
      // ...
  }
  ```
  `PrivateStoreOperation` is the generated extensible-enum struct (`Generated/Models/PrivateStoreOperation.cs`) and has no `ToRequestContent` method.

### Root cause (MPG generator source)

- **Microsoft.Generator.CSharp.ClientModel** / `ParameterContextRegistry` emits `.ToRequestContent(payload)` for any non-primitive body parameter.
- **SerializationVisitor** (http-client-csharp-mgmt) only synthesizes the `ToRequestContent` helper on MRW model types (via the implicit-operator rename). Extensible-enum / union structs (and other non-MRW body types) never get this helper method generated.

Result: any TypeSpec operation that passes a `union` / extensible-enum as `@bodyRoot` produces code that fails to compile.

### Current workaround (Marketplace SDK)

A hand-written partial is shipped to supply the missing method so the generated code compiles:

```csharp
// sdk/marketplace/Azure.ResourceManager.Marketplace/src/Customize/Models/PrivateStoreOperation.cs
public readonly partial struct PrivateStoreOperation
{
    internal static RequestContent ToRequestContent(PrivateStoreOperation? payload)
    {
        if (payload == null) return null;
        return RequestContent.Create(payload.Value.ToString());
    }
}
```

Alternative workaround: `@@alternateType(...payload, string, &#34;csharp&#34;)` — but this erases the strongly-typed enum from the public API surface, which is undesirable.

### Repro command

```powershell
cd sdk\marketplace\Azure.ResourceManager.Marketplace
dotnet build /t:GenerateCode /p:LocalSpecRepo=&#34;...\specification\marketplace\resource-manager\Microsoft.Marketplace\Marketplace&#34; /p:SaveInputs=true
# Without the SDK-side partial, `dotnet build` fails with CS0117 on the Post/Delete methods.
```

### Expected behavior

The MPG generator should emit `ToRequestContent` (or equivalent request-body serialization) for **all** non-primitive body types it emits the call site for — including extensible-enum / union structs — or otherwise route non-MRW body serialization through a type-agnostic helper (e.g. `RequestContent.Create(payload.Value.ToString())` inline at the call site).

### Impact

Any TypeSpec MPG spec that uses an extensible-enum / union as a body parameter will fail to compile out-of-the-box and require a hand-written SDK-side partial to unblock code generation.
